      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/23/1",
      "text": [
        " شَهَادَةِ اَلزُّورِ قَالَ \"إِذَا كَانَ اَلشَّيْءُ قَائِماً بِعَيْنِهِ رُدَّ عَلَى صَاحِبِهِ وَ إِنْ لَمْ يَكُنْ قَائِماً ضَمِنَ بِقَدْرِ مَا أَتْلَفَ مِنْ مَالِ اَلرَّجُلِ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3331 - Muhammad ibn Abi Umayr narrated from Jamil ibn Darraj from Abu Abdullah (as), regarding false testimony.\nImam (as) said: \"If the thing is present in its original form, it is returned to its owner. But if it is no longer present, then the false witness is liable for the value of what he caused to be lost from the man's property.\""
        ]
      }
    },
